UserRoleCapability

public UserRoleCapability(java.lang.String userName,
                          java.lang.String fullUserName,
                          java.lang.String role,
                          java.lang.String capability)
Constructs an UserRoleCapability instance populated with the specified information. While this constructor will allow you to populate an UserRoleCapability instance with invalid data, the use of such instances is not recommended and they may cause problems if they are passed to other API methods.

Parameters:
userName - User's login ID.
fullUserName - User's full name.
role - Role definition name.
capability - Capability: "P" (Primary), "S" (Secondary), "L" (Leader) or "T" (Temporary).
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if capability is null or more than one character long.
